        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="757" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–547: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-05">April 5,
                            1947</date>.]<lb/>[Received April 5—7:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from Tientsin:</p>
                <p>59, April 5. Remytel 47 [<hi rend="italic">57</hi>], April 5. Following press
                    release issued this afternoon by Marine Headquarters: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>It has been definitely established that a Communist organization attacked
                            the Marine ammunition point near Tangku at 0115 on the morning of the
                            5th of April. Papers found on dead Chinese soldiers in the area verified
                            the fact. It appears that this attack was made for the purpose of
                            securing ammunition, but little if any was obtained.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Nanking as 59; repeated to Peiping. Smyth.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
